item.title: CVE-2021-43550|2024-08-04T04:03:08.513Z -- philips -- efficia%20cm%20series
item.description: The use of a broken or risky cryptographic algorithm is an unnecessary risk that may result in the exposure of sensitive information, which affects the communications between Patient Information Center iX (PIC iX) Versions C.02 and C.03 and Efficia CM Series Revisions A.01 to C.0x and 4.0.
